# Git & Commit Conventions

## Commit messages — English only

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change, no behavior change |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `docs` | Documentation |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps |
| `perf` | Performance |
| `ci` | CI/CD |

Examples:

```
feat(web): add pad sidebar layout
fix(api): handle 401 in auth client
test(h5): add login form smoke test
```

- Subject: imperative mood, ≤50 chars, no period at end
- Scope: `h5`, `web`, `ui`, `api`, `shared-types`, or omit

## Before commit

```bash
pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm audit
```

Fix critical/high audit findings before merging.

## Do not

- Chinese commit messages
- Vague messages: `fix bug`, `update`, `wip`
- Commit `.env`, secrets, or `dist/` artifacts
